 THE PILOT OF A GRUMMAN AA1B, EXPERIENCED A LOSS OF CONTROL WHILE 
LANDING. THE PILOT STATED HE FLARED TOO HIGH AND FAILED TO ADD POWER IN 
TIME TO SOFTEN THE LANDING.  THE AIRCRAFT EXITED THE LEFT SIDE OF THE 
RUNWAY INTO A SNOW BANK AND NOSED OVER. 
 1) THE PILOTS IMPROPER FLARE MANEUVER; 2) HIS FAILURE TO PERFORM A 
BOUNCED LANDING RECOVERY; AND 3) HIS FAILURE TO MAINTAIN DIRECTIONAL 
CONTROL OF THE AIRCRAFT. 
